## Minimum Quality Threshold

<Callout type="warning">

Games that receive an average rating **below 1 star** will **not be approved** for publication. This policy is in effect as of March 2026.

</Callout>

If your game does not meet the minimum 1-star threshold, the following process applies:

1. **Thread closed** - your approval thread will be closed and locked.
2. **7-day improvement window** - the thread remains locked for 7 days, giving you time to improve your game.
3. **Resubmission** - after 7 days, you can resubmit your game for a new review cycle.

This is not a permanent rejection. The goal is to help creators raise quality and give every game the best chance to succeed.

## Category Placement Guidelines

Categories are updated weekly.

### New Releases

- All games with a 1+ star rating receive a New Release tag.
- **3 Stars** - Prioritized placement in *featured* and top positioning.
- **2 Stars** - May appear in weekly releases if space allows, otherwise placed lower.
- **1 Star** - Always placed at the bottom of New Releases, unless sorted by Newest.

### Burst Games

- Priority given to 3-star games.
- 2-star games may appear if popularity drives demand.

### Stake Exclusives

- Priority given to 3-star games.
- 2-star games may appear if driven by popularity.
